Veteran Nollywood Nigerian actress, Kate Henshaw, has been named of the judges for a new international talent show, scheduled to air in the United States. Henshaw shared the news and her excitement on her verified Instagram page. She revealed she was one of 50 judges from all over the world, who were called, “Wall Of The World.” <img class="aligncenter wp-image-843281 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243.jpg 768w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-640x360.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-320x180.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-281x158.jpg 281w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-562x316.jpg 562w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-531x299.jpg 531w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-1062x598.jpg 1062w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-487x274.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Kate-Henshaw-and-Fellow-Judge-Rupaul-e1548495292243-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> The new show called The World’s Best is produced by the same studio that handles The Big Bang Theory and Criminal Minds, CBS.
The reality TV series, touted as the biggest talent show in the world, will be hosted by Emmy Award winner James Corden. The American judges include country singer Faith Hill, actress Drew Barymore and Tv personality Rupaul and the show would be on CBS, premiering in the U.S on Feb 3rd following the Super Bowl. This event features elite acts from around the globe competing for a $1 million prize. The acts not only have to impress the all-star line-up of American judges, they also need to break through the “wall of the world,” featuring more than 50 renowned experts from 38 different countries.   Totally excited to finally announce that I am one of the International judges, proudly representing Nigeria in the New CBS Global talent show "THE WORLD'S BEST"!! The biggest and best new talent show. It's like nothing you have seen before!! Together with 49 other International judges we make up the #WallOfTheWorld. American judges are Drew Barrymore, Faith Hill and RuPaul Show host is James Corden It premieres in the U.S on Feb 3rd following the Super Bowl on CBS… Stay tuned for more info!!! Spot the Nigerian Flag @Theworldsbest @theworldsbestcbs #WorldsBest #WallOfTheWorld #K8DGR8 #OluwaKate #LevelUp A post shared by  Kate Henshaw (@k8henshaw) on Jan 24, 2019 at 10:25am PST 